Release Notes for Seq66 v. 0.99.24 2026-04-15 "What a Qt, 6!"

This release contains fixes and updates for Qt as well as
a number of other issues discovered.

-   Main window and grid.
  - At startup, instead of setting argv[0] as app-info, get
    the executable's path from Qt.
  - Now uses the populate\_midich\_combo() function.
- Event editor.
  - A new button for either Control or Program changes pops
    up the menus for Control Changes and Program Changes.
  - Various fixes to controller and patch naming and handling.
- Added the populate\_midich\_combo() function to the
  qt5helpers module.
- Added the drums module for GM/non-GM drum notes.
- Palettes.
  - Updated the incrypt-66.palette file.
- Fixed some Qt6 deprecations.
- Documentation updated. Additional pictures for Event editor.
- Moved the LICENSE files to "licenses" sub-directory.

See NEWS for many more details.

